At 89, Opal Lee walked from Texas to D.C. to get Juneteenth declared a federal holiday.

She’s now 93 and just delivered 1.3 million petition signatures in support of Juneteenth.

@SenMarkey and I introduced the Juneteenth legislation, and we had the honor of meeting her. https://t.co/GPz4UrrJ8j

Working together &amp; across the aisle is how you get things done in the Senate. I teamed up w/
@SenatorFischer to help make sure all Americans can access mental health services, especially during
#COVID19. Read abt our bipartisan bill in our @rollcall op-ed: https://t.co/Gq5HPz34jX

Called into radio stations in Minnesota this morning with 
@RepDeanPhillips. 

Went well but this picture kind of looks like a stock photo at a business meeting. https://t.co/7SMfjIVfFQ

UPDATE: just yesterday, researchers presented a new report on how serious the maternal mortality crisis is for rural areas.

@StarTribune has the story and it’s just devastating. We need to ensure mothers everywhere can access high quality health care.

https://t.co/LzRJDt4dYm https://t.co/ct8wnFCZTp

I really enjoyed talking to Northfield business owners with 
@RepAngieCraig.  

Great to hear how these local leaders strengthen their community as I continue my rural listening tour. https://t.co/bBtdXVa2im

I stand in solidarity with the men and women of the 
@UAW who are fighting for fair pay and benefits, and secure jobs. 

When workers stand together to fight for better wages and working conditions, they lift each other up. Speak out. Be strong.

The U.S. Women's Soccer team hasn’t finished below 3rd place in the World Cup. Funny, that's also the best the men’s team ever did, once.

&amp; @USWNT games have raked in GREATER total revenue than the men's team recently, yet the women are paid much LESS.

@USSoccer, what gives?! https://t.co/6gDvUezboG

Since when is $20 BILLION in revenue considered financial hardship? 

@EPA’s decision to grant a waiver to exempt Exxon Mobil from RFS requirements is bogus. This abuse destroys biofuel demand and—at the end of the day—hurts Minnesota ag and our economy.

